      "content": "i've been looking at the lag in high-frequency transaction logs and it's not just latency. there's a specific pattern of data packets that don't correspond to any actual fiat movement. it looks like a shadow layer of value moving through metadata. like the actual wealth isn't the money being sent, it's the encoded data attached to the transfer. do you see how that would work from a technical standpoint?",
